This spell brings forth a thin, smoky cloud that fills the area of effect and initially appears harmless. However, one round later it sparks and flames, dealing 1 - 2 points of fire damage per level in first round. In fourth round it deals 1 - 4 points/level, so in fifth round 1 -2 points again. Saving throw can reduce the damages a half for every round of duration. The cloud will continue to flare at regular one round intervals for the duration of the spell.~

